// §6.3 + §7.3 — re-annotating an already-tagged value with its own
// type is a no-op. `x as Result` where x already has type Result
// does NOT require `named`; it preserves identity (§7.3 preservation
// table: "as T (named T adopted as the same T) — ✓ identity").
Result is tagged union ok as string, err as string

x is "hello" as Result named ok
// Re-annotation — no `named` needed
y is x as Result

// Both bindings are the same value
check_equal is x is y
check_tag is x is named ok
